er \\\" +\\n                    \\\"of runnable entities running on the available processors averaged over a period of time\\\")\\n                .register(registry);\\n        }\\n\\n        if (systemCpuUsage != null) {\\n            Gauge.builder(\\\"system.cpu.usage\\\", operatingSystemBean, x -> invoke(systemCpuUsage))\\n                .tags(tags)\\n                .description(\\\"The \\\\\\\"recent cpu usage\\\\\\\" of the system the application is running in\\\")\\n                .register(registry);\\n        }\\n\\n        if (processCpuUsage != null) {\\n            Gauge.builder(\\\"process.cpu.usage\\\", operatingSystemBean, x -> invoke(processCpuUsage))\\n                .tags(tags)\\n                .description(\\\"The \\\\\\\"recent cpu usage\\\\\\\" for the Java Virtual Machine process\\\")\\n                .register(registry);\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private double invoke(@Nullable Method method) {\\n        try {\\n            return method != null ? (double) method.invoke(operatingSystemBean) : Double.NaN;\\n        } catch (IllegalAccessException | IllegalArgumentException | InvocationTargetException e) {\\n            return Double.NaN;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    @Nullable\\n    private Method detectMethod(String name) {\\n        requireNonNull(name);\\n        if (operatingSystemBeanClass == null) {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n        try {\\n            // ensure the Bean we have is actually an instance of the interface\\n            operatingSystemBeanClass.cast(operatingSystemBean);\\n            return operatingSystemBeanClass.getDeclaredMethod(name);\\n        } catch (ClassCastException | NoSuchMethodException | SecurityException e) {\\n            return null;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    @Nullable\\n    private Class<?> getFirstClassFound(List<String> classNames) {\\n        for (String className : classNames) {\\n            try {\\n                return Class.forName(className);\\n            } catch (ClassNotFoundException ignore) {\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return null;\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777693199841}]}\n885:[tool-call] delta {\"command\":\"git diff -- tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/src/test/java/io_micrometer/micrometer_core/ProcessorMetricsTest.java && git status --short\",\"timeout\":10}\n886:[tool-call] end id=call_mfm3Pg08W5PsaT0MN39wStPI|fc_0c9577e12a477c7e0169f57227c7f481948d71ec4b7783ccf2 name=bash args={\"command\": \"git diff -- tests/src/io.micrometer/micrometer-core/1.8.2/src/test/java/io_micrometer/micrometer_core/ProcessorMetricsTest.java && git status --short\", \"timeout\": 10}\n887:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Finalizing note**\\n\\nI should make sure to include a concise note since I didn’t run the process as instructed. I wonder if inspecting the git diff could help clarify what changes have been made. That might be useful to understand what I need to do next. It’s always a little tricky ensuring everything is captured correctly, but focusing on these steps will definitely help streamline the process. I’ll aim to keep it straightforward!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0c9577e12a477c7e0169f5722577a88194a924446c1604e763\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp9XInCf5QwjgNbx_-14KzpsEFo5KD6CbfBEulymGAr6zV84KcIUk2ENZqPCpxP_14sa2EQv6ILVKEl905JUwEDpLlYy4fyDEten66co8ICsRgVpo8mdOA0NoUC2d4B21WScsZV7yWHs7ONTu9Cj1GS5adAJ4HV4J1GAnIITI0C7lf1vrdV_fqxSLtRB55yJyDy5EK7b3sRolpOw_20ndr1Pc_1gIfcnkQvi4OmspQPMErE32yD46dcvhN0UejVurrWWSb7jynDfL8B39ps2OtnKQ4et07-F41ReefJ-dRq3Orerh162rCRNe31wpRasYekgP67fNixMn_gF9XvxRegdszZq4f5YNIXD1vRlLN6W4vmRL-IzTq2qokq95mg_c5844QKDu3JXBOCXTrBY8g3-eMjwc-Y5OIMpbX6d0Z4Z49mK_LrI6mbPJcsfi6H1RfcbsqJQ0KPl9NM_Drc5nbzXfJVNGbp1N5oqIAPsQo412omZA9ypDDU82TPAcOsLM9LgL7AF6Xcj4XD5dtAaIj2zyG5woK-4XtevEHikKR3tzvlp_lqebmGEf-k04Jm78Zj9wgwMfEp5ZUO